metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, SENSIBLE SHOES 2017 is more basic than the typical song, having below average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.

SENSIBLE SHOES 2017 is written in the key of C Lydian.

Music written in Lydian often emphasizes this difference by creating melodies that feature this note.  Due to the dissonant interval between the 1st and 4th scale degrees, Lydian is less common in popular music.

metadata.editComments:
Hi folks,

Here is the 2017 edition of the yr8 demo song. SENSIBLE SHOES.

This year is a little different as I've been trialling some new support software. Band in a Box 2017 has been added to the course and it is working alongside HOOKTHEORY+ (subscription) and FINALE.

The process involves test programming the composition in HOOKTHEORY for ease of editing and the ability to view a class full of work with multiple saves showing their progress and process. 

This is then transferred to Band in a Box by typing in the chords, selecting styles and refining the structure.

Returning to HOOKTHEORY the lyric melody line is transferred to Band in a Box via MIDI, and can be edited in FINALE if required (more on this later).
